<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="924" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d924">
                    <head>Dr. Carl Hilton</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chur</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 24, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                    <p>The undersigned most cordially approves of the Swiss address of sympathy to
                        the United States, and requests to contribute his signature to its columns
                        of subscribers in our native land.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dr</hi>. CARL HILTON,</signed>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Lawyer in Chur</hi>.</closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>